      <description>There are many different methods for serializing data in Java. We&amp;rsquo;ll quickly look at three of them.
XML via JAXB Java includes a special API known as the Java Architecture for XML Binding , or JAXB, for mapping Java objects to XML.
To use it, we can add a few annotations to our objects:
import javax.xml.bind.annotation.*; @XmlRootElement public class Person { // other code omitted }In the simplest form, we simply add the @XmlRootElement annotation above the class to denote that it can be treated as a root element.</description>
